flowRoot.flowPara: D is a programming language combining power, performance and productivity.

D is a multi-paradigm programming language that combines a principled approach with a focus on practicality. In D you get to harness the power and high performance of C and C++ and also the safety and programmer productivity of modern languages such as Ruby and Python. Special attention is given to the needs of quality assurance, documentation, portability, and reliability. The D language is statically typed and compiles directly to machine code. It supports many programming styles: imperative, object oriented, and metaprogramming. Itâ€™s a member of the C syntax family, and its appearance is very similar to that of C++.
D is the culmination of decades of experience implementing compilers for many diverse languages, and attempting to construct large projects using those languages.
